CERN: LHCb experiment reports observation of exotic pentaquark particles</title>
					<description>Today, the LHCb experiment at CERN's Large Hadron Collider has reported the discovery of a class of particles known as pentaquarks. The collaboration has submitted a paper reporting these findings to the journal Physical Review Letters.</description>
